column17: As the Operations Manager I was responsible for all staffing of the warehouse and inside sales personnel.  Overseeing the daily processing of customer orders.  Responsible for managing and coordinating the purchase of goods and services for the company in a most   efficient and economical matter.  Expedite orders when required, following up on order progress and resolving any discrepancies.  Interview incoming sales representatives, and stay abreast of new changes in the industry or market.  Update vendor and customer files, checking invoices, and rebid contracts as needed.  Act as a liaison between the purchasing department and the general accounting department at our home office.  Obtain pricing, specifications, and sources of supplies for our budgeted projects.  Maintain and update product, service, vendor, and catalogue files.  Dispose of company assets which are no longer needed or are obsolete, including the processing of all associated  forms and paperwork.  Perform administrative functions, including transferring calls from the switchboard, filing, and greeting customers.  Proofread incoming orders for completeness, and to be error free.  Assist in faxing purchase orders and bid request.    February 13, 2009    To Whom it may concern    I write this letter as a recommendation for Mark French. While Mark was with JGB Enterprises for only a few months his contribution to the effort was immediate and the learning curve minimal. It was only due to an economical reduction in our workforce that resulted in Mark leaving JGB.    As the Operations Manager, Mark managed the warehouse staff as well as overseeing the daily processing of orders, inventory management and was involved in customer service.    Mark’s organizational skills are one of his biggest assets.    Mark is a versatile worker and I would recommend him highly for employment with your company. Please feel free to contact me at the office if you have any questions.    Sincerely,        Kevin Donovan  Midwest Region Manager  JGB Enterprises  314-487-3144
